    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-16T16:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-16T16:35:00-05:00" n="803"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d803">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">794.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/8–1954:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 803<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Japan</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d803fn1">Drafted and approved for transmission in <gloss
                            target="#t_NA1">NA</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-16T17:35:00-04:00"
                            >September 16, 1954—5:35 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>588. Tokyo also pass <gloss target="#t_CINCFE1">CINCFE</gloss>. Your despatch
                        241.<note n="2" xml:id="d803fn2">See telegram 363 from Tokyo, <ref
                            target="#d789">Document 789</ref>.</note> Japanese request orally
                    transmitted through Japanese Embassy that $40 million section 550 yen be
                    utilized procure naval vessels Japan for Japanese forces discussed Defense and
                        <gloss target="#t_FOA1">FOA</gloss>. This yen fund earmarked for payment
                    existing <gloss target="#t_MDAP1">MDAP</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_OSP1"
                        >OSP</gloss> contracts. Therefore Japan proposal procure additional items
                    not presently programmed Japan not acceptable since diversion dollar funds from
                    other <gloss target="#t_MDAP1">MDAP</gloss> projects would be required.</p>
                <p>In view Japanese concern prospect reduced dollar receipts <gloss
                        target="#t_MDAP1">MDAP</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_OSP1">OSP</gloss>, Defense
                    agrees instruct <gloss target="#t_FEC1">FEC</gloss> make payments against
                    contracts 50 percent dollars 50 percent yen until $40 million yen fund
                    exhausted.</p>
                <pb facs="0672" n="1728" xml:id="pg_1728"/>
                <p>Estimate total outstanding <gloss target="#t_MDAP1">MDAP</gloss>/<gloss
                        target="#t_OSP1">OSP</gloss> contracts $88.5 million basis total contracts
                    placed FY1952 through FY1954 less payments made through July 31.</p>
                <p>Japanese Embassy informed this proposal at regular meeting economic section
                    September 16.</p>
                <p>Defense and <gloss target="#t_FOA1">FOA</gloss> concur this message.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
